ZH: 我的生日礼物是一本新书。
EN: My birthday gift is a new book.

ZH: 他送给我一个漂亮的项链作为礼物。
EN: He gave me a beautiful necklace as a gift.

ZH: 她喜欢收到花朵作为礼物。
EN: She likes receiving flowers as gifts.

ZH: 我们准备了一些小礼物给客人。
EN: We have prepared some small gifts for the guests.

ZH: 请接受这份小小的礼物表示感谢。
EN: Please accept this small gift as a token of appreciation.

ZH: 这种礼物很有心意。
EN: This gift is very thoughtful.

ZH: 我们和她约好不交换礼物。
EN: We agreed not to exchange gifts with her.

ZH: 礼物并不在乎贵重，关键是心意。
EN: The value of a gift is not important, the thought behind it is.

ZH: 她总是能挑选出别人喜欢的礼物。
EN: She always knows how to pick out gifts that others will like.

ZH: 这个季节最受欢迎的礼物是围巾。
EN: Scarves are the most popular gifts this season.

ZH: 他们送来了许多礼物，让我感到非常惊喜。
EN: They brought many gifts that surprised me.

ZH: 每个人都期待着收到礼物。
EN: Everyone looks forward to receiving gifts.

ZH: 在这个特殊的日子里，我会给你一个特殊的礼物。
EN: On this special day, I will give you a special gift.

ZH: 我从他那里得到了一份特别的礼物。
EN: I received a special gift from him.

ZH: 我们正在为公司员工准备一些新年礼物。
EN: We are preparing some New Year gifts for the company employees.

ZH: 作为一个小孩，接到礼物真的很开心。
EN: As a child, receiving gifts really brings joy.

ZH: 礼物不在于价值，而在于用心。
EN: The value of a gift is not in its price, but in the thought behind it.

ZH: 她的生日礼物是一顶漂亮的帽子。
EN: Her birthday gift is a beautiful hat.

ZH: 我们应该感激每一个送给我们礼物的人。
EN: We should appreciate everyone who gives us gifts.

ZH: 小狗玩具是儿童们最喜欢的礼物之一。
EN: Puppy toys are one of the favorite gifts for children.
